snippet.title: Amber Heard poses with crutches after sustaining 'a broken bone'  | ABS US  DAILY NEWS
snippet.description:
‚òÖMore ABS NEWS - Entertainment Video‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ 
 She was recently spotted after a 'flirty' date with Sean Penn.But things quickly took a turn for the worse for Amber Heard, 31, who took to Instagram on Thursday to let fans know she had sustained 'a broken bone'.But the Justice League actress seemed in high spirits despite her misfortune, happily posing with friends - and her crutch.¬†The Machete Kills actress posted a selfie to Instagram that she took inside the hospital while having scans for the fracture.In the picture, Heard poses with a crutch while wearing a fedora and flashing one shapely pin from under her hospital gown.   She captioned the post 'Crutching MRI-chic'.In another pic the All The Boys Love Mandy Lane poses with friends and her crutch.This image is captioned: 'Note: never let a broken bone get in the way of good dinner party.'¬†  She reportedly enjoyed a 'flirty' date with actor Sean Penn at the Sunset Tower Bar in Los Angeles on Saturday.And Amber  looked deep in thought when she was pictured at the Silverlake Farmers' Market the morning after.Sporting tousled hair, it was the first sighting of the actress since she shared a bottle of red with Madonna's ex.¬†The Drive Angry starlet looked incredible in her casual get-up on Sunday, wearing a tan colored cropped suede jacket and cropped jeans.She wore one of her trademark cowboy hats and hid her eyes behind a pair of round-lens sunglasses.Completing her look with a pair of black Alias Mae ankle boots, the ex-wife of Johnny Depp also carried a small black leather bag on one shoulder.

The woman took an all-time low and faked bruises so as to make Johnny look like he was in the wrong. In fact, she used this at court, in the year 2016, to file a restraining order against Depp which truly shows how low the woman could stoop to. If you guys are curious about what the complaint that she filed stated, it was all lies and no truth. She stated that he hurt her by flinging her iPhone at her right eye causing her to receive a blue eye which she was donning that day.

Now, what evidence against this lie was brought up?
But the truth always does come out and it did. Johnny and his team delivered footage dating back to that same day where she was in the elevator and guess what? No bruises at all.  
So basically she just wanted to paint Depp as the bad guy in a series of events and then finally be able to get all of his money.

Do you guys think the lies stopped here?
Of course not! Amber Heard‚Äôs sister, Whitney Heard was seen sporting bruises once upon a time. On being questioned about it, she didn‚Äôt wish to speak about it as she wasn‚Äôt comfortable doing so. 

The recent events involve her sister Whitney, siding with Amber in one of her other lies. This lie included Johnny assaulting his sister due to his apparent anger issues to which he denied. 

On further investigation, a large sum of money had recently been transferred from Amber‚Äôs account to Whitney‚Äôs account. Could it have been a bribe Amber gave to Whitney for covering her tracks? Was it Amber that had been the one that actually hit Whitney?

Well, this is what Johnny‚Äôs team thinks because he has taken a stand that he did not do such a thing at all. 

Was Kate James also involved in the part of Amber‚Äôs lies?
For those of you who do not know who Kate James is, Kate James was a former personal assistant of Amber Heard. She has seen a side of Amber‚Äôs that many didn‚Äôt. They were quite friendly initially which resulted in Kate opening up to her boss and sharing the traumatic story of her past which involved her facing an assault while she was in Brazil in her early 20‚Äôs.

Amber took no remorse to Kate‚Äôs feelings, modified the story, and played the narrative of the story as if it was her own. This totally destroyed Kate causing her to come out and speak against this in 2020. Clearly, everyone was scared of Amber, and it took them some guts and willpower to finally come onto the pedestal to use their story, their voice, and the truth to put Amber down. 

But, what was the real reason why Roberta Kaplan withdrew herself from offering her services to Amber Heard?
Renowned American lawyer, Roberta Kaplan, has been fighting with Amber‚Äôs team for quite a while now. She finally decided to withdraw herself from the team in 2020 stating it was due to logistic and travel difficulties due to the ongoing pandemic that is causing her difficulty in meeting the needs of the team as well as Amber‚Äôs. It was not only her who withdrew from the team, but many other members too did leave the team and the case. 

The drama did not end here. The biggest evidence that exposed her entirely were the leaked audio tapes from 2015 which came out to the public only in 2020. This was the biggest evidence against her where she claimed Depp to be an assaulter and one due to whom she had to face a series of domestic violence. The audiotape included her differentiating between a hit and a punch trying to defend herself so weakly that even the judges weren‚Äôt convinced with the crapload of lies that she was fumbling to say. She eventually gave in and stated she did hit him.

From all these facts we can clearly state that Amber Heard had some real anger issues and was in dire need of anger management. Due to her not seeking help, she tended to take out all her frustration towards her marriage and other close ones around her, who will be the only ones to provide a description of the kind of person Amber really was. 

The people of the industry and the world were most angry due to the fact that she took advantage of the MeToo movement to get Depp into trouble, causing both his personal and professional life to shatter to pieces. aquaman 2

snippet.title: Amber Heard Is Being Investigated For Potential Perjury In 2015 Dog Smuggling Incident
snippet.description:
In 2015, actress Amber Heard was charged with bringing then-husband Johnny Depp‚Äôs two Yorkshire terriers into Australia illegally. The case was closed back then, but now, Heard is being investigated for allegedly committing perjury during the dog smuggling incident.

The allegations came out during Depp‚Äôs libel lawsuit last year against a British tabloid. During that case, Depp‚Äôs former estate manager testified that Heard asked him to lie under oath for her after she was charged with illegally importing the dogs into Australia. As E!News reported, Heard didn‚Äôt obtain a permit for the dogs prior to bringing them into the country on a private jet and without having them quarantine for two weeks.

‚ÄúAfter Australian‚Äôs agriculture minister threatened to have the dogs euthanized unless they ‚Äòbuggered off back to the United States,‚Äô Depp and Heard had the dogs flown back, again on a private jet,‚Äù E!News reported. ‚ÄúFacing the prospect for a maximum 10-year prison sentence, the actress pleaded guilty to a lesser charge of falsifying a travel document to sneak the dogs into the Australia. Her lawyer told the court the actress was jetlagged, worried about a hand injury that Depp suffered during filming Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales, and believed her assistants had sorted out the paperwork for the dogs.‚Äù

snippet.title: Lost Sky - Fearless pt.II (feat. Amber Heard) [MCM Release]
snippet.description:
Music used in this video
Lost Sky - Fearless pt.II (feat. Chris Linton) [NCS Release]

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in a minor supporting role in the sports drama Friday Night Lights (2004), followed by a series of other small roles in television and film. Her first leading role was in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), but it was not released in the United States until 2013 due to distribution problems. Her second major role came in the short-running The CW television series Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in the action film Never Back Down and the stoner comedy Pineapple Express, both box-office successes. The same year, she received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Heard continued her career with roles in films such as The Informers (2008), The Stepfather (2009), Zombieland (2009), and The Joneses (2009). In 2011, she played the female lead opposite Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and opposite Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary. Subsequently, Heard appeared in 3 Days to Kill (2014), Magic Mike XXL (2015) and The Danish Girl (2015). She also starred in the indie film The Adderall Diaries (2015), the television musical drama One More Time (2015), and the Martin Amis adaptation London Fields (2018). The latter was due to be released in 2015, but became the subject of a series of lawsuit between its director, Heard, and the film's production company over its editing and other issues.

In 2017, Heard acted as part of an ensemble cast in the indie film I Do...Until I Don't (2017) and made an appearance as Mera in the superhero film Justice League (2017). She reprised that role opposite Jason Momoa in Aquaman (2018), the most profitable DC Extended Universe film up to that point, and the fifth highest-grossing film of 2018.[2][better source needed] The same year, Heard was named a global spokesperson for the cosmetics giant L'Or√©al Paris. In 2019, she appeared in supporting roles in the independent films Her Smell and Gully, and in 2020, she starred in the miniseries The Stand, an adaptation of Stephen King's novel.[undue weight? ‚Äì discuss]

Heard engages in activism for causes such as LGBTQ rights and domestic and sexual violence awareness. She is an American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) ambassador[undue weight? ‚Äì discuss] and has been named a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.

Heard was married to her Rum Diary co-star Johnny Depp from 2015 to 2017. Their divorce drew significant media attention as Heard alleged that Depp had physically and verbally abused her during most of their relationship. In 2019, he sued her for defamation after she publicly discussed being a victim of domestic violence, alleging that she had been the abusive party; Heard denied this. Depp also sued the publishers of The Sun in a related libel suit, with Heard as a key witness for the defendants. In November 2020, the High Court of Justice of England and Wales ruled that Depp had lost his case and that the majority of Heard's allegations had been proven to a civil standard. Depp intends to appeal.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Lifestyle 2020, Income, House, Cars, Girlfriend, Family, Net Worth, Divorce, Johnny Depp
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Lifestyle 2020, Income, House, Cars, Girlfriend, Family, Net Worth, Divorce, Johnny Depp

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. Born and raised in Texas, she made her film debut in a minor supporting role in the sports drama Friday Night Lights (2004), followed by a series of other small roles in television and film. Her first leading role was in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), but it was not released in the United States until 2013 due to distribution problems. Her second major role came in the short-running The CW television series Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in the action film Never Back Down and in the stoner comedy Pineapple Express, which were both box office successes. The same year, she received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Heard continued her career with roles in films such as The Informers (2008), The Stepfather (2009), Zombieland (2009), and The Joneses (2009). In 2011, she played the female lead opposite Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and opposite Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary; neither were critically nor commercially successful. Subsequently, Heard appeared in 3 Days to Kill (2014), Magic Mike XXL (2015) and The Danish Girl (2015). She also starred in the indie film The Adderall Diaries (2015), the television musical drama One More Time (2015), and the Martin Amis adaptation London Fields (2018). The latter was due to be released in 2015, but became the subject of a series of lawsuit between its director, Heard, and the film's production company over disagreements in its editing and other issues. The film was finally released in 2018, and was both a critical and commercial flop.

In 2017, Heard acted as part of an ensemble cast in the indie film I Do...Until I Don't (2017) and made an appearance as Mera in the superhero film Justice League (2017). She reprised the latter role opposite Jason Momoa in Aquaman (2018), which became the most profitable DC Extended Universe film up to that point, and the fifth highest-grossing film of 2018.[3] The same year, Heard was also named a global spokesperson for the cosmetics giant L'Or√©al Paris. In 2019, she appeared in supporting roles in the independent films Her Smell and Gully. In addition to her acting career, Heard engages in activism for causes such as LGBTQ rights and domestic and sexual violence awareness. She is an American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) ambassador and has been named a Human Rights Champion for the Stand Up for Human Rights campaign by the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights.

Heard was married to her Rum Diary co-star Johnny Depp from 2015 to 2017. Their divorce drew significant media attention as Heard alleged that Depp had been physically and verbally abusive towards her through most of their relationship. In 2019, he sued her for defamation after she publicly discussed being a victim of domestic violence, alleging that she had been the abusive party; Heard denied this. Depp also sued the publishers of The Sun in a related libel suit, with Heard as a key witness for the defendants. In November 2020, the High Court of Justice of England ruled that Depp has lost his case and that the majority of Heard's allegations had been proven to a civil standard which Depp intends to appeal.

snippet.title: Amber Heard - Lifestyle, Boyfriend, Family, Net worth, House, Car, Age, Biography 2020
snippet.description:
Actress and model whose claim to fame came in 2008 with lead roles in Pineapple Express and Never Back Down. She received additional fame after staring in The Stepfather, The River Why, The Ward, Drive Angry, The Rum Diary, and Magic Mike XXL. In 2018, she was cast as Mera in Aquaman.She was very involved in her high school's drama department before dropping out at age 17 to pursue modeling. She starred in the short-lived TV series The Playboy Club. She came out as bisexual at the 25th anniversary GLAAD event. She was married to actor Johnny Depp from 2015 until they filed for divorced just over a year later. In 2017, she began dating Elon Musk; however the two separated later that same year. In late 2019, she began dating Bianca Butti. Nicolas Cage costarred with her in Drive Angry.
